hazard /ˈhæzəd/

(hazarding,hazarded,hazards) 

1. N-COUNT A hazard is something which could be dangerous to you, your health or safety, or your plans or reputation. 危险 

例： A new report suggests that chewing gum may be a health hazard. 一份新的报告指出，嚼口香糖可能给健康带来危害。 

2. V-T If you hazard or if you hazard a guess , you make a suggestion about something which is only a guess and which you know might be wrong. 大胆猜测 

例： I would hazard a guess that they'll do fairly well in the next election. 我大胆猜测，他们在下次选举中将会有不俗的表现。

</div>

